*
(Please type a command or say `\end')
*Proof Idea

*The mechanism that makes the proof work.

*
(Please type a command or say `\end')
*Proof

*A clear and rigorous derivation, written to preserve the main flow of the argu
ment.

*
(Please type a command or say `\end')
*PZoom Boxes

*Optional zoom-ins at proof pain points. These boxes supply local sub-proofs or
 missing intermediate steps without cluttering the main proof.

*
(Please type a command or say `\end')
*Guiding Principle

*
(Please type a command or say `\end')
*Keep the main proof elegant. Reveal the hidden steps where they matter.

